### Version

Yosys 0.53+39 (git sha1 388955031, aarch64-apple-darwin23.5-clang++ 18.1.8 -fPIC -O3)

### On which OS did this happen?

macOS

### Reproduction Steps

Transferring from discussions https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/discussions/5136

1. Create a file blinky.sv with the content below.

2. Run the command ``yosys -p "synth_gowin -top blinky -json _output.json" -q blinky.sv``



blinkey.sv:
```
module blinky #(
    // Num of click cycle per led toggle.
    parameter integer DIV = (27000000 / 2)
) (
    input        sys_clk,
    output logic led       // Active low
);

  // ---- Reset generator.

  logic [3:0] reset_counter = 0;
  logic sys_reset = 1;

  always_ff @(posedge sys_clk) begin
    if (reset_counter < 3) begin
      sys_reset <= 1;
      reset_counter <= reset_counter + 1;
    end else begin
      sys_reset <= 0;
    end
  end

  // ---- Blinker

  reg [31:0] blink_counter;

  always_ff @(posedge sys_clk) begin
    if (sys_reset) begin
      blink_counter <= 0;
      led <= 1;
    end else if (blink_counter < (DIV - 1)) begin
      blink_counter <= blink_counter + 1;
    end else begin
      blink_counter <= 0;
      led <= ~led;
    end
  end

endmodule
```

### Expected Behavior

Yosys completes with no warnings.

### Actual Behavior

The following warning is printed

```
Warning: Ignoring boxed module $paramod\ALU\ALU_MODE=s32'00000000000000000000000000000010
```

